Someone in the world dies in a traffic accident, on average, every 30 seconds.
That is the conclusion of the international group Make Roads Safe, a worldwide
effort to make road safety a global priority. On 31 March 2008, the United
Nations plans to take up the issue of global road safety amid calls for a U.N.
conference to tackle the rising toll of road deaths and injuries. VOA's Tetiana
Koprowicz has more on efforts to improve road safety in the U.S.
 
 
